<h2>
    Introduction to Bass Fishing in Oregon
</h2>
<p>
    Bass fishing might not be the first thing people associate with the Pacific Northwest, but Oregon—and especially areas near <strong>Beaverton</strong>—offers a surprisingly rich bass fishery. From hidden urban ponds to expansive lakes and warmwater rivers, there's no shortage of great spots to chase both largemouth and smallmouth bass.
</p>
<h3>
    Growth of Bass Fishing in the Pacific Northwest
</h3>
<p>
    Once seen as a warmwater oddity in salmon country, bass fishing in Oregon has grown into a beloved pastime. Today, it draws thousands of anglers across the state thanks to expanding habitats and effective fisheries management.
</p>
<h3>
    Why Beaverton Is a Great Starting Point
</h3>
<p>
