</p>

<h2>
    Types of Bass Found Near Beaverton
</h2>
<h3>
    Largemouth Bass
</h3>
<p>
    These are the most commonly targeted bass species around Beaverton. You'll find them in lakes and ponds with ample vegetation and structure like lily pads, sunken logs, and boat docks.
</p>
<h3>
    Smallmouth Bass
</h3>
<p>
    Preferring rocky, flowing water, smallmouth bass are typically found in the Willamette River and Columbia River system. They’re known for their aggressive strikes and aerial acrobatics.
</p>
<h3>
    Hybrid and Spotted Bass
</h3>
<p>
    While less common, some nearby waters have reports of spotted bass or hybrid variations. These fish can be found in deeper, clearer reservoirs with rock and gravel beds.
</p>
